The need for bone repair and insight into new regeneration therapies as well as 
improvement of existing regeneration routes is constantly increasing as a direct 
consequence of the rise in the number of trauma victims, musculoskeletal 
disorders, and increased life expectancy. Bisphosphonates (BPs) have emerged as 
a class of drugs with proven efficacy against many bone disorders. The most 
recent ability of this class of drugs is being explored in its anti-cancer 
ability. However, despite the pharmacological success, there are certain 
shortcomings that have circumvented this class of the drug. The mediation of 
